<BaseLayout lastUpdated="2026-07-07" author="InkFlow Team">
  <SEOHead slot="head" title="InkFlow vs Square Appointments for Tattoo Studios" description="Square Appointments costs $110-140/mo with integrations. InkFlow includes deposit booking, waivers, and aftercare. Start free." canonical="https://ink-flows.com/compare/square-appointments/" />
  <FAQSchema questions={[
    { question: "Can Square Appointments handle tattoo studio booking?", answer: "Square Appointments handles basic scheduling but lacks tattoo-specific features: deposit-based booking (Square uses card-on-file), digital consent forms, multi-artist commission splitting, ink/needle inventory tracking, and aftercare automation. You'd need Square for Payments, Square for Retail, and third-party tools to cover what InkFlow offers in one platform." },
    { question: "Is Square Appointments free for tattoo studios?", answer: "Square Appointments has a Free plan with basic scheduling, but you'll quickly need Square Payments (2.6% + $0.10), Square for Retail ($60/month for inventory), a separate waiver app ($35-50/month), and an aftercare tool ($15-30/month). The total cost of 4+ Square products and integrations typically exceeds InkFlow's paid plans while still missing tattoo-specific workflows." },
    { question: "Does Square have tattoo waiver forms?", answer: "No. Square does not offer digital tattoo waivers or consent forms. Studios must integrate third-party waiver software and manually sync client data between systems â€?creating data fragmentation and additional monthly costs." },
    { question: "Should I use InkFlow or Square for my tattoo studio?", answer: "Choose InkFlow if you want one platform that handles booking, deposits, waivers, commission splits, inventory, aftercare, and CRM â€?purpose-built for tattoo. Choose Square if you already use Square for retail payments and don't mind managing 3-4 separate tools and dealing with data fragmentation." },
  ]} />
