                <td class="p-4 text-center text-accent-300">{row.i}</td>
                <td class="p-4 text-center text-gray-500">{row.b}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Is Best For -->
  <section class="border-t border-ink-800/50 py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Who Is Square Best For?</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">Square is a strong choice for <strong class="text-white">solo artists and walk-in studios</strong> that already use Square for payments and don't need tattoo-specific features. The free Square Appointments plan plus Square Payments gives you basic scheduling and payment processing at zero subscription cost. If your studio is simple, you're one person, and clients walk in rather than book online, Square works fine.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-400">Square also excels if you sell retail products (t-shirts, aftercare products) alongside services â€?their POS ecosystem is mature and reliable for retail inventory.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Who Is InkFlow Best For?</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">InkFlow is built for <strong class="text-white">tattoo studios that want one platform</strong> instead of 4+ tools. You're a good fit if you need:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-gray-400">
          <li class="flex gap-2">â€?<strong>Deposit-based booking</strong> â€?collect real payments at booking, not just card-on-file</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">â€?<strong>Digital waivers</strong> â€?included in all plans, no third-party integration needed</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">â€?<strong>Multi-artist commission</strong> â€?auto-calculated per artist per transaction</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">â€?<strong>Ink/needle inventory</strong> â€?without paying $60/mo for Square Retail</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">â€?<strong>Aftercare automation</strong> â€?check-ins at day 3/7/14 + healed photo requests, see <a href="/features/tattoo-aftercare-software-automation" class="text-accent-400 hover:underline">aftercare automation features</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">Related: <a href="/compare/mindbody" class="text-accent-400 hover:underline">InkFlow vs Mindbody</a> Â· <a href="/compare/vagaro" class="text-accent-400 hover:underline">InkFlow vs Vagaro</a> Â· <a href="/pricing" class="text-accent-400 hover:underline">See pricing</a></p>
